<td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> PoV hunting</span><hr size=1> Since the patch last week, mobs have been increased in risk.  Some of the things that are good to know:  <br>
<br>
1.  Mobs are really resistant (malo/tash are good things)<br>
<br>
2.  Most spiders are flagged immune to root, Crawlers(centipede looking) are about a 50/50 chance imunne to root.  Finally, golems are always rootable but somewhat resistant and high in breaking roots earlier.<br>
<br>
3.  Aggro range has increased so pulling one might bring 2-3 (/frowns).  BA and Niivag know really well how to hunt the desert mobs on top send them a tell.<br>
<br>
4.  Beware of trains. PoV has taken DL/KC to another level, so be safe.<br>
<br>
